text:
*challenges* 
•  logo detection and button positioning was the most challenging part, and the fact that it’s also global issue, companies like amazon faced the same issue, and they invested on teams andbuilt huge  infrastructure for over coming this problem.
• the challeng was all the available solutions work as api and we can’t risk our sensitive data to be sent to third parties, also the available models need to be trained on large amount of data to solve the issue besided it will cost time and money to do that. 
*proposed solution:*
• we used a creative way that maixmize the quality of results while minimizing the cost, 
• we used template matching method wich is available in opencv library.
• we gave the model a picture of the logo and aske it to locae it’s position on the image.
• we extracted the starting coordination  points of the logo in the image plus the hight and the width of it.
• the result was more than 60% of the logo positions was detected ,and more than 80% of engagement buttons was detecte also.
*future recommendations* 
• train our own model to get accurate results
• we should use yolo 7 as a model
